'''Arrowroot''', or '''obedience plant''', (''Maranta arundinacea'') is a large perennial herb found in [[rainforest]] habitats. Arrowroot is also the name for the easy-to-digest starch from the rhizomes (rootstock) of West Indian arrowroot. This plant should not be confused with Sagittaria species sometimes called "arrowhead" and used as a root vegetable.

